This paper is about frequent itemsets mining, which is a common task in data mining and database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Database) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents a new approximation algorithm and an algorithm for approximating top-$k$ frequent itemsets, which are related to data structures and algorithms, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are also likely sub-categories. The paper uses probabilistic techniques to analyze the error bounds of sampling algorithms, which is related to artificial intelligence and machine learning, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the efficiency of the algorithms, which is related to computational complexity and optimization, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category.
